\section{Layout and semantics}{

\code{multinom} coefficients render per non-reference outcome (one labelled
block per outcome level); \code{exponentiate = TRUE} yields relative-risk
ratios (RRR, the Stata \verb{mlogit, rrr} convention). AME reports the
marginal effect on each outcome's probability (per-outcome columns).
\code{mlogit} renders per-alternative rows; AME is refused
(\pkg{marginaleffects} has no \code{slopes()} method for its
one-row-per-alternative data format).
}

\section{Robust variance}{

\code{multinom}: classical only. \code{mlogit}: \verb{HC*} (it provides \code{estfun}) and
\verb{CR*} via \code{sandwich::vcovCL}; the cluster vector must be at the
choice-situation level (one entry per individual), and a long-format
cluster errors with a clear message.
}

